snippet: The ambassador had been recalled and missions were closed after a wave of protests by Egyptians against the detention of an Egyptian lawyer in Saudi Arabia.
abstract: Saudi Arabia’s ambassador, Ahmed Qattan, returns to Egypt a week after the Saudi government closed its embassy there in response to protests over the arrest of Ahmed el-Gizawy, an Egyptian human rights lawyer, in Saudi Arabia; Qattan's return follows days of feverish diplomatic efforts by Egyptian military rulers and politicians to heal the relationship between the two countries.
lead_paragraph: The ambassador had been recalled and missions were closed after a wave of protests by Egyptians against the detention of an Egyptian lawyer in Saudi Arabia.
